{"key":"post-8601113","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>8601113</id>\n<content>I cringe when people say not to mist cakes.&amp;nbsp; It's absolutely essential to mist the cakes.&amp;nbsp; You want enough air exchange for proper fruiting, which means your cakes or other substrates will begin to lose moisture. . .also a major pinning trigger.&amp;nbsp; You must mist to replace that moisture.&amp;nbsp; Mist the cakes, and mist the perlite.&amp;nbsp; There is no need to mist the sides.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>8601130</next>\n<prev>8600690</prev>\n<first>8600649</first>\n<last>8601146</last>\n<when>1215378905</when>\n<utime>07/07/08 12:15 AM</utime>\n</post>"}